INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1807, 4, '2013-06-23 18:44:49', '2013-06-23 18:44:49', 'Once a new account is opened with Interactive Brokers, funds management, such as depositing, withdrawing, and transferring cash and positions into and out, is administered through Account Management. Use your login credentials to log into Account Management from the Login menu on the<a title="Interactive Brokers" href="https://gdcdyn.interactivebrokers.com/sso/Login" target="_blank"> Interactive Brokers web site</a>.\n\n.', 'How do I deposit, withdraw and transfer funds and positions?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-close-my-account', '', '', '2013-06-23 18:44:49', '2013-06-23 18:44:49', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1807', 20, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1826, 4, '2013-06-23 20:40:06', '2013-06-23 20:40:06', '"Our mission is to serve individuals and small businesses by simplifying investing and by managing personalized portfolios at low cost."', 'What is your Mission Statement?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'when-are-the-fees-taken-out', '', '', '2013-11-26 14:52:18', '2013-11-26 14:52:18', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&#038;p=1826', 19, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1827, 4, '2013-06-23 20:40:29', '2013-06-23 20:40:29', 'Yes. Invessence accepts discretionary authority to manage the assets in the client’s account. We assume investment authority on the client’s account when the investment management agreement is executed. Clients always retain individual ownership of all securities.', 'Does Invessence have investment discretion over my account?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'are-there-any-penalties-for-closing-my-account', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:40:29', '2013-06-23 20:40:29', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1827', 17, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1828, 4, '2013-06-23 20:41:08', '2013-06-23 20:41:08', 'In the simplest terms, Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs) are investment products that track indexes like the S&amp;P 500, Dow Jones or NASDAQ-100 Index at a minimal cost. When you buy shares of an ETF, you are buying shares of a portfolio that tracks the yield and return of its underlying index. The main difference between ETFs and other types of index funds is that ETFs don\'t try to outperform their corresponding index, but simply replicate its performance. They don\'t try to beat the market, they try to be the market.', 'What is an ETF?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-the-difference-between-an-etf-and-mutual-fund', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:41:08', '2013-06-23 20:41:08', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1828', 14, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1829, 4, '2013-06-23 20:41:35', '2013-06-23 20:41:35', 'Invessence does not take custody of client assets. Client assets are held with a registered broker dealer that is a qualified custodian. Clients will receive statements directly from their account custodian on a monthly basis.\r\n\r\nInvessence has chosen Interactive Brokers Group, a subsidiary of IBG LLC group, as a complete turnkey solution for trading, clearing and reporting and a qualified custodian for client\'s assets. On a consolidated basis, Interactive Brokers Group’s equity capital exceeds $4.8 billion and is rated “A-/A-2; Outlook Stable” by Standard and Poor’s Research. Customer securities accounts at IB are protected by the Securities Investor Protection Corporation (“SIPC”).\r\n\r\nInvesting involves risk and unless otherwise stated, are not guaranteed.', 'Is my money safe with Invessence?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'besides-stocks-and-bonds-what-other-types-of-assets-are-in-my-portfolio', '', '', '2013-11-26 14:51:48', '2013-11-26 14:51:48', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&#038;p=1829', 18, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1830, 4, '2013-06-23 20:42:12', '2013-06-23 20:42:12', 'As part of our risk management program, each account is reviewed at least quarterly. We review the asset mix, risk level, and account restrictions in relation to the client’s investment objectives, current position size and specific holdings. The frequency of the reviews depends on market conditions and other factors that a prudent, professional investor would deem necessary. Account objectives are confirmed, at least annually, with our clients.\n\nWritten research reports will be issued to clients on a periodical basis. These reports disclose performance returns, security holdings and market values. If a client desires, other relevant factors may also be disclosed.', 'How often does Invessence review my account?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-does-auto-rebalancing-work', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:42:12', '2013-06-23 20:42:12', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1830', 15, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1831, 4, '2013-06-23 20:42:37', '2013-06-23 20:42:37', 'Invessence will analyze and rebalance an existing portfolio at least quarterly because market movements may cause your initial weightings to change. Invessence will automatically rebalance the portfolio to maintain this optimal strategy over time.', 'How does auto-rebalancing work?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-if-i-want-to-change-my-asset-allocation', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:42:37', '2013-06-23 20:42:37', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1831', 16, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1833, 4, '2013-06-23 20:43:29', '2013-06-23 20:43:29', 'Invessence is an online investment advisor that provides a cost-effective alternative to traditional investment management. Our web-based platform provides any individual, small business, or organization the ability to create and manage a personalized investment plan. Invessence empowers its clients by removing the complexity of the financial markets and constructs a professionally selected portfolio of low-cost Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs). Instead of trying to fit a client into a specific “model” portfolio, we consider each client’s individual needs and create a portfolio based on their own specific risk tolerance and time horizon.', 'What type of service does Invessence provide?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-does-tax-reporting-work', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:43:29', '2013-06-23 20:43:29', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1833', 1, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
