INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1834, 4, '2013-06-23 20:43:48', '2013-06-23 20:43:48', 'Invessence charges an investment management fee of 0.25% (per annum) for all accounts of $100,000 or greater. For accounts smaller than $100,000, Invessence charges an investment management fee of $250 (per annum).\n\nAdvisory fees are billed monthly, in arrears; and, are inclusive of trading costs, such as brokerage commissions and transactions charges, and related fees and expenses associated with the executing and clearing of a client\'s trades. Neither Invessence nor any of its related or associated persons or affiliates receives or participates in any of the brokerage commissions or transactions charges charged to or incurred by a managed client account. There are no \'soft dollar\' arrangements currently in place to pay for research used to service client accounts.\n<p align="justify"><span style="font-family: Arial;"> </span></p>', 'What does Invessence cost?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'when-do-i-receive-my-tax-statements', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:43:48', '2013-06-23 20:43:48', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1834', 8, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1835, 4, '2013-06-23 20:44:16', '2013-06-23 20:44:16', 'There are two main customers, or account types:\n<ol>\n	<li>Single - An individual is classified as individual, joint (two individuals), trust and IRA (Traditional/Rollover/Roth/Inherited/SEP).</li>\n	<li>Organization - An organization is classified as a corporation, partnership, limited liability corporation (LLC), or unincorporated business.</li>\n</ol>\nInvessence offers the following account structures, which reflect your business:\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<a href="http://www.invessence.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Screen-Shot-2013-11-04-at-10.42.42-AM.png"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-2666" alt="Screen Shot 2013-11-04 at 10.42.42 AM" src="http://www.invessence.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/Screen-Shot-2013-11-04-at-10.42.42-AM.png" width="483" height="309" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;', 'What type of accounts do you offer?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-the-difference-between-a-traditional-and-roth-ira', '', '', '2013-06-23 20:44:16', '2013-06-23 20:44:16', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=1835', 7, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2668, 2, '2013-11-04 11:54:58', '2013-11-04 16:54:58', 'Although we rely heavily on our technology to help build your portfolio, our goal is to not replace the human interaction. We still believe investing is a personal business and encourage potential clients to reach out to our friendly investment consultants directly by email (sales@invessence.com) or phone (201) 977-4567.', 'How do I get started?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-get-started', '', '', '2013-11-04 11:54:58', '2013-11-04 16:54:58', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2668', 5, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2670, 2, '2013-11-11 11:04:00', '2013-11-11 16:04:00', 'Formed in 2012, Invessence is an independent Registered Investment Advisor based out of New Brunswick, New Jersey. Our firm is committed to helping people pursue their financial goals. We have access to a wide range of financial products and services for individuals and business owners. We believe the information we provide will better enable you to identify your goals and make sound decisions to help reach them. As of November 2013, we are serving clients in New Jersey, New York, Connecticut and Illinois.\r\n\r\nAs an independent, our clients benefit from our ability to offer unbiased investment advice in achieving their financial goals. Since Invessence is not affiliated with any brokerage firm, we do not receive commissions on the products we recommend. As a RIA, we have fiduciary responsibility to always put the interest of our clients first and to respect the trust place us.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Who is Invessence?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'who-is-invessence', '', '', '2013-11-26 14:47:32', '2013-11-26 14:47:32', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&#038;p=2670', 0, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2674, 2, '2013-11-11 11:08:29', '2013-11-11 16:08:29', 'A <b>Registered Investment Adviser</b> is an Investment Adviser registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission or a state\'s securities agency. Individuals or firms that receive compensation for giving advice on investing in securities such as stocks, bonds, mutual funds, or exchange traded funds are generally deemed to be investment advisers.\r\n\r\nInvessence is based out of New Jersey and is registered as an investment adviser in several states including Connecticut, New York, New Jersey, and Illinois.', 'What does it mean to be a Registered Investment Adviser?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-does-it-mean-to-be-a-registered-investment-advisor', '', '', '2013-11-26 14:50:12', '2013-11-26 14:50:12', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&#038;p=2674', 2, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (3499, 3, '2013-11-26 14:51:22', '2013-11-26 14:51:22', 'Invessence does not take custody of client assets. Client assets are held with a registered broker dealer that is a qualified custodian. Clients will receive statements directly from their account custodian on a monthly basis.\n\nInvessence has chosen Interactive Brokers Group, a subsidiary of IBG LLC group, as a complete turnkey solution for trading, clearing and reporting and a qualified custodian for client\'s assets. On a consolidated basis, Interactive Brokers Group’s equity capital exceeds $4.8 billion and is rated “A-/A-2; Outlook Stable” by Standard and Poor’s Research. Customer securities accounts at IB are protected by the Securities Investor Protection Corporation (“SIPC”).\n\nInvesting involves risk and unleAll securities involve risk and may result in loss. Not an offer, solicitation of an offer, or advice to buy or sell securities in jurisdictions where Invessence is not registered.', 'Is my money safe with Invessence?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '1829-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-11-26 14:51:22', '2013-11-26 14:51:22', '', 1829, 'http://www.invessence.com/?p=3499', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2675, 2, '2013-11-11 11:10:30', '2013-11-11 16:10:30', 'This means that we are required to act solely in the best interest of our clients, even if that interest is in conflict with our own financial interest. RIAs must disclose any conflict of interest, or any potential conflict of interest, to our clients before and throughout a business engagement.\n\nThis requirement includes making a full disclosure of all compensation received, both the amount and the source not only of investment management, but also of any commission, any "soft-dollar" arrangements, or any special incentives to recommend one product or service over another.', 'What is meant by a Fiduciary Standard?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'what-is-meant-by-a-fiduciary-standard', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:10:30', '2013-11-11 16:10:30', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2675', 3, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2677, 2, '2013-11-11 11:13:24', '2013-11-11 16:13:24', 'Our current minimum portfolio size is $5,000.', 'Do you a have minimum portfolio size?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'do-you-a-have-minimum-portfolio-size', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:13:24', '2013-11-11 16:13:24', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2677', 9, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2679, 2, '2013-11-11 11:21:18', '2013-11-11 16:21:18', 'Each client has his own separate brokerage account at <a title="Interactive Brokers website" href="https://www.interactivebrokers.com/en/main.php" target="_blank">Interactive Brokers</a>. Invessence does not take custody of your assets but utilizes the brokerage services of Interactive Brokers, a registered broker dealer and FINRA member.\n\nAs a registered investment advisory firm, Invessence has a fiduciary responsibility to seek best execution for client transactions. Clients are not under any obligation to effect trades through Interactive Brokers. Invessence will endeavor to accommodate specific client requests to custody assets at another broker dealer.\n\nInvessence has reviewed the Interactive Broker platform and recommends Interactive Broker based on a number of factors. These factors include the financial strength of the broker dealer, the broker’s transaction confirmation and account statement practices, trade clearance and settlement capabilities. Other factors include Invessence’s experience with Interactive Broker, the broker’s reputation, and the quality of execution services including state of the art Smart order routing and low transaction and custodial costs.\n\nAs a fiduciary, Invessence has the responsibility to effect orders correctly, promptly and in the best interests of our clients. In the event any error occurs in the handling of any client transactions due to Invessence’s actions, or inaction, or actions of others, Invessence’s policy is to seek to identify and correct any errors as promptly as possible without disadvantaging the client or benefiting Invessence in any way.\n\nIf the error is the responsibility of Invessence, any client transaction will be corrected and Invessence will be responsible for any client loss resulting from an inaccurate or erroneous order.\n\nInvessence’s policy and practice is to monitor and reconcile all trading activity, identify and resolve any trade errors promptly, document each trade error with appropriate supervisory approval and maintain a trade error file.\n\nIf a trade error results in a profit to an unintended client account, at the cost of another Invessence client account, an offsetting financial transaction will be used to rectify the aggrieved party. The end result will be that no client benefits or suffers as a result of the error.', 'How does brokerage work with Invessence?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-does-brokerage-work-with-invessence', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:21:18', '2013-11-11 16:21:18', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2679', 4, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2680, 2, '2013-11-11 11:23:52', '2013-11-11 16:23:52', 'Reports of all Client account activity, including an inventory of investments and listing of transactions, are available from Interactive Brokers on a daily, monthly and yearly basis via the “Account Management” menu on their website (www.interactivebrokers.com).\n\nAn account statement from Interactive Brokers will include: Net Asset Value Time Series, Mark-to-Market Performance Summary in Base, Realized and Unrealized Performance Summary in Base, Cash Report, Change in Position Value, Long Open Positions, Trades, Other Fees, Deposits and Withdrawals, Interest Accruals, Broker Interest Paid, Security Information, Codes, and Legal Notes.\n\nIf you experience any account login issues or need to reset a password, you can call Interactive Brokers Customer Service at 877 442 2757.', 'How do I view my account statement?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-view-my-account-statement', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:23:52', '2013-11-11 16:23:52', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2680', 13, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2683, 2, '2013-11-11 11:45:56', '2013-11-11 16:45:56', '<ol>\n	<li><a title="Register" href="http://www.invessence.com/signup.xhtml" target="_blank">Register</a> a new account with Invessence.</li>\n	<li>You will receive an email that contains a link to open an account  - in your own name - at our preferred firm Interactive Brokers.</li>\n	<li>Complete the online application form along with the funding step. You may fund their account by transferring assets from an existing investment account, a bank, or any other source.</li>\n	<li>You will receive an email with documents from us. Please retain these for your reference. Please complete, sign and return the Investment Advisory Contract and return to us (by email/fax/postal mail).<a href="http://www.motiwalacapital.com/documents/Acknowledgment%20of%20Disclosure%20Documents.pdf">\n</a></li>\n	<li>Once funded, we will confirm your investment portfolio with you and invest your money.</li>\n</ol>', 'How do I open an account with Invessence?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-do-i-open-an-account-with-invessence', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:45:56', '2013-11-11 16:45:56', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2683', 6, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2684, 2, '2013-11-11 11:50:54', '2013-11-11 16:50:54', 'Yes, you have full access to your own account at all times. We ask that you discuss all account changes with us in advance when possible to decide if the move is in your best interest based on the long-term goals we established for you.', 'If you are managing my account, can I still make my own trades in my account?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'if-you-are-managing-my-account-can-i-still-make-my-own-trades-in-my-account', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:50:54', '2013-11-11 16:50:54', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2684', 12, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2685, 2, '2013-11-11 11:53:06', '2013-11-11 16:53:06', 'No, Invessence is not a broker-dealer and does not charge you each time we rebalance your portfolio. We are a fee-only advisor and do not charge per transaction. Our only fees come from a percentage of assets (0.25%) or a flat rate of $250, based on your account size.', ' Do you charge for individual stock/ETF trades?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'do-you-charge-for-individual-stocketf-trades', '', '', '2013-11-11 11:53:06', '2013-11-11 16:53:06', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&amp;p=2685', 11, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (2687, 2, '2013-11-11 11:56:13', '2013-11-11 16:56:13', 'No, we believe that mutual funds charge high fees, are tax-inefficient, and can lag their benchmark indices. We prefer to use low cost Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs).  ETFs provide the same diversity as mutual funds, but offer many other advantages, price is only one.', 'Do you invest through mutual funds?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'do-you-invest-through-mutual-funds', '', '', '2013-11-26 15:03:31', '2013-11-26 15:03:31', '', 0, 'http://www.invessence.com/?post_type=icompany_faq&#038;p=2687', 10, 'icompany_faq', '', 0) ; 
