INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (302, 6, '2013-04-30 11:24:53', '2013-04-30 11:24:53', '[heading type="h2" margintop="8px" marginbottom="28px" bordered="yes" align="left"][color]Mission Statement[/color][/heading]\n\n[heading type="h4"][floated float="left " clear="no"][/floated]We empower individual investors in achieving financial stability by simplifying the complexity of the markets and reducing the significant costs of investment management through a personalized and disciplined plan.[/heading]\n\n[heading type="h2" margintop="0px" marginbottom="28px" bordered="yes" align="left"][color]Management Team[/color][/heading]\n\n[heading type="h4"][floated float="left " clear="no"][/floated]Invessence provides a cost-effective alternative to professional investment management. Our team is comprised of innovators in trading, portfolio management, sales &amp; marketing, and technology.[/heading]\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[one_third last="no"][person designation="CEO" name="Mary Lou Giustini" picture_path=""]Mary Lou Giustini has more than three decades of experience working in the financial services industry. Before co-founding InvEssence, Mary Lou spent 35 years with Merrill Lynch, the last years, as a Managing Director of the sales and trading team, serving the largest institutional client base in the U.S. mid-west region. Her sales and management expertise resulted in top tier industry rankings for client service and revenue production. Professionally a champion of customer service and personally a leader in the community, Mary Lou serves on the Board of the US Fund for UNICEF, Chicago Financial Women\'s Association, a member of the National Association of Professional Women, Security Traders Association of Chicago and House Ambassador for Ronald McDonald House Charities.\n[/person][/one_third]\n\n[one_third last="no"][person designation="President" name="Jigar Vyas" picture_path=""]Jigar has over 20 years of experience in traditional asset management, hedge fund management, securities brokerage business and technologies. He has pioneered new techniques in transaction cost analysis, anti-gaming algorithms for trading and portfolio management (patent pending). He was a senior trader and quantitative strategist at J P Morgan and worked with asset management group, which managed $100 billion in assets. He was a portfolio manager at hedge fund EVA Advisers and co-founded Chatham Capital Management. Prior to coming to Wall Street Jigar was a senior engineer at Raytheon Co, working on U.S. Navy satellite program. Jigar holds a B.S. in Electrical Engineering from Rutgers and a Masters in Computer Engineering from Boston University.\n[/person][/one_third]\n\n[one_third last="yes"][person designation="Chief Operating Officer" name="Paresh Shah" picture_path=""]Paresh has over 25 years of experience in technology industry covering product development and management. He has delivered enterprise-wide software products &amp; solutions for Telecom, Government, Healthcare, and Financial domains. He has also established and managed technology joint ventures. Bringing many years of his technology expertise, operations management skills and entrepreneurial insight to Invessence, Paresh looks after daily operations and ensures that all systems are efficient and effective.\n[/person][/one_third]\n\n[one_third last="no"][person designation="Chief Technology Officer" name="Prashant Mehta" picture_path=""]Prashant has more than 25 years of experience in project management, technology development and database management. For the past 16 years, he has been developing trade processing systems, end of day positions and data warehouse management. He holds a bachelor’s degree in computer science from Rutgers University.\n[/person][/one_third]\n\n[one_third last="no"][person designation="Chief Business Strategist" name="Michael Frank" picture_path=""]Michael has over 30 years’ experience in capital markets. He started his career as an options market maker on the Philadelphia Stock Exchange. In 1984 he moved to the American Stock Exchange where he was a key builder of Rockrimmon Securities. The firm grew from 3 people to over 50 employees spanning all option exchanges. In 1995 Michael, a Partner at Rockrimmon, left to found Gateway Partners. At Gateway he planned the overall growth strategy of the firm to become a leading options specialist with market making operations on all five option exchanges. In 2001, Michael sold his specialist business to Knight Capital Group. Michael received a B.S. in Business Management from Farleigh Dickinson University.\n[/person][/one_third]\n\n[one_third last="yes"][person designation="Head of Business Development" name="Christopher Lengle" picture_path=""]Since 2002, Chris has worked at brokerage, asset management and financial technology firms delivering a broad range of innovative financial products and investment support solutions. He is responsible for the firm\'s strategic partnerships and leading business development efforts in driving new revenue opportunities for the firm. He holds a B.A. in both Economics and Psychology from Georgetown University.\n[/person][/one_third]\n\n<!--\n[one_half last="no"]<strong></strong>\n\n[heading type="h2" margintop="28px" marginbottom="28px" bordered="yes" align=" left"]Why we are [color]Special[/color][/heading]\n\n[floated float="left"][fontawesome icon="suitcase" size="extralarge" style="normal" color="dark"]     [/floated]InnoCompany offers very reliable bootstrap framework loaded with advanced features like [popover type="link" placement="top" title="A Popover title..." linktext="Click to open Popover"] Content goes here. You can place popovers like this anywhere you want... [/popover] and [tooltip link="http://themeforest.net/?ref=worthapost" tooltip_text="Click here to visit themeforest.net"]tooltips[/tooltip] and much more. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, sum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam. Sum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipisci